narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a great section. The readings can be a little dense, but they spark interesting discussion. The written assignments are very manageable, and you have a lot of freedom to choose your topics. If you like psychology and/or writing, take this course.
I would definitely recommend Professor Yost's English 114. She was a terrific instructor and I believe my academic writing has improved significantly over the course.
English 114 with Julia Yost is the best course I have taken this semester. What makes it special is certainly the instructor, who is amazingly articulate and extremely interesting.
It's a good class and interesting if you enjoy the topic of madness and civilization.

I would recommend this class, especially for those interested in psychology or mental illness specifically. The discussions in class were interesting; the topics were thought provoking. Sometimes the readings were lengthy/dense. The atmosphere of the class was nice and energetic though. The work load is very manageable. The rough drafts, peer revisions, and feedback from Julia are very helpful.
i would recommend this course to a fellow student. This class will introduce you to college level writing and strengthen you intellectually.

I would recommend this course if you're looking for a basic course to improve your writing. However, if you feel that you already have a strong writing background from high school, it's not really necessary that you take 114.
I would highly discourage students from taking a course tought by this instructor.
I would recommend English 114 to another student because the seminar style is very engaging and if you are someone who likes discussions then class is enjoyable.
